Many thanks to the following individuals (in alphabetical order):

* azesmbog
    1. For validating tests on real hardware.
    2. For his research on the unstable flag behavior of the "ccf/scf"
       instructions.
    3. For his invaluable help.
* Banks, David (hoglet)
    For his research on the flag behavior of the "ccf/scf" instructions [1].
* Brady, Stuart
    For his research on the flag behavior of the "ccf/scf" instructions [2].
* Greenway, Ian
    For testing the flag behavior of the "ccf/scf" instructions on real hardware
    [2,3].
* Helcmanovsky, Peter (Ped7g)
    1. For writing the "Z80 CCF SCF Outcome Stability" test [4].
    2. For his research on the unstable flag behavior of the "ccf/scf"
       instructions.
* Nicolás-González, César
    For helping me to research the unstable flag behavior of the "ccf/scf"
    instructions.
* Rak, Patrik
    1. For cracking the flag behavior of the "ccf/scf" instructions [5,6].
    2. For writing the "Zilog Z80 CPU Test Suite" [6,7].
* Woodmass, Mark (Woody)
    * For his research on the flag behavior of the "ccf/scf" instructions [8].


